The Independent Republic of Azerbaijan played the founder’s role for the liberation of the Azarbaijan people from the Ottoman Empire, which expressed its military aid in the liberation war. At the same time, the fact that the republic did not play a significant role in the establishment of avant-garde states - Caucasian Muslim Central Committee, Transcaucasian Democratic Federative Republic and the First Republic of Armenia that subsequently declared war to Azerbaijan, is noteworthy. Moreover, it is well known that during Sovietization the Azerbaijan SSR addressed the Soviet leader with the request to place the city of Baku on the Turkish grounds, as a result of which it became the center of the “Muslim rear” and the only center in the USSR that was a local main Bykist.

The current state of our country, especially in the north is associated within the Azerbaijan Republic. The idea of the unification - “Eternal Union of the Two Independent Azerbaijan” is the oldest idea with which we associate the creation of the independent Azerbaijani state 12th century. For at this time, Azerbaijani unity reigned from the Black Sea to India. The greatest Azerbaijani, as well as Turk, as a matter of fact, figure is 4th Shah ibn Jalaladdin, whose real name is “Ayaz”.
